revision.text:
{{Italic title}}
'''''A la poupée''''' is an [[intaglio (printmaking)|intaglio printmaking]] technique for applying different ink colors using a ball-shaped wad of fabric to apply the ink to a [[copperplate etching|copperplate]]. Paper is printed through just one run in the press. The term ''a la poupée'' means "with a doll", which refers to the wad of fabric, shaped like a ball.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nga.gov/exhibitions/clrflimpr-tech.shtm | title=Colorful impressions: Techniques | publisher=National Gallery of Art | accessdate=March 25, 2015 }}</ref>

